_header: Not long ago purposed I and thought
Subjects: complaints, lovers’; lovers, addresses to beloved
_description: A lover’s complaint — five stanzas rhyme royal

DULCosVii13.First Lines:
Not long a goo purposyd I and thoughtTo breken of pleynly frome
                    lusty luffes daunce…
DULCosVii13.Last Lines:
…But shortly to say I ame aye þat manThat you wyll serue
                    as suffise and can
